  <summary>3/9/1995--Introduced.
Amends the Export Administration Act of 1979 to allow any person who is injured in his or her business or property by reason of a violation of the anti-boycott provisions of such Act to bring a civil action against the U.S. person who committed such violation. Provides a civil penalty for each violation.</summary>
